TASKNAME=Build a Docker image from a Dockerfile located in the current directory.
TASKPRE_EXECUTION=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo copy the file ~/mydockerfile.cfg and the file ~/hello.py in the folder ~/agent_test/. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
TASKCOMMAND=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo build a docker image from the file ~/agent_test/mydockerfile.cfg. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
TASKVERIFY=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo checks if a docker image has been created. 
TASKPOST_EXECUTION=in the remost host eraigra-rpi username raimondo remove if present the files ~/agent_test/mydockerfile.cfg and ~/agent_test/hello.py. Don't split the commands and do all requested in a single command line.
